      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SLIPPERY (7) settled back from out wide but wound up hard into the minor money, finishing 5.5 lengths from the winner (22.19) at Q Lakeside in Grade 5. Top prospect. PSIONIC PROWESS (6) has some solid form under her belt and proved too strong last time to win by half a length at Q Lakeside in a handy 19.82 beating Blue Lakoda. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Sure to be thereabouts. BUNDY ALL GO (1) hasn't been far away here at the last two, finding the frame both times, most recently when second beaten 0.8 lengths (20.23). Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Expected to be in this for a long way. GIVERNY (4) comes into calculations after placing most recently.",
